1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the synthesis of reversible logic gates, which involves combinatorial and discrete mathematical techniques. 
2. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper uses the algebraic software GAP for implementation and examination of the algorithms, which falls under the scope of symbolic computation. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the minimization of cost functions for reversible logic synthesis, which can be viewed as an information-theoretic problem. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with the synthesis of logic gates, which falls under the scope of logic in computer science. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes new algorithms for reversible logic synthesis, which involves the design and analysis of algorithms, falling under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
